This project was to create an AI that could play the two player game Othello. Starter code was given (othello_game.py, othello_gui.py, and othello_shared.py) to implement the 
game in code. The assignment was to create an AI that would generate moves given a particular board state. The assignment involved creating functions to examine game trees,
includings ones that could perform the minimax algorithm and alpha-beta pruning algorithm. Improvements were made to the algorithms by implementing state caching and node
ordering. The assignment also involved creating a custom heuristic function to judge how good a particular board state was. The heuristic function gives a result based on
different weighted parameters. The heuristic function was improved by continuously adjusting the weights of each parameter and training on (playing against) slightly different 
versions of the heuristic function, to find the better function depending on the winner of each game. The functionality of the code was tested using an autograder 
(autograder.py) and an AI that made random moves (randy_ai.py).
